answers.textarea_17284500:
2 eggs
2 1/2 cups milk
2 cups flour
8 ounce cream cheese
2 teaspoons vanilla extract
1 cup white sugar
answers.textarea_17284501:
1. Preheat oven to 325 degrees F.
2. Mix milk, cream cheese and sugar.
3.  Add eggs one at a time, blending well.
4. Add vanilla and flour
5. Bake for 60 minutes, or until cake jiggles evenly across the top when lightly shaken.

answers.textarea_17284500:
1 pound spaghetti
8 ounces bacon
coarse salt and ground pepper
3 large eggs
3/4 cup grated Parmesan cheese
1/2 cup half-and-half
answers.textarea_17284501:
1. Set a large pot of water to boil (for pasta).
2. In a large skillet, cook bacon over medium heat until crisp (around 8-12 minutes)
3. Salt boil pasta and cook until al dente
4. in a large bowl, whisk together eggs, Parmesan, and half-and-half
5. Drain pasta and add to egg mixture. Add bacon; season with salt and pepper.

answers.textarea_17284500:
1/2 baguette
3 ounces blue cheese
2 tablespoons honey
answers.textarea_17284501:
Thinly slice the baguette.
Place the rounds on a baking sheet and broil until golden brown (about 1 1/2 minutes per side)
Divide the blue cheese among the toasted bread slices.
Drizzle 2 tablespoons honey evenly over them.

answers.textarea_17284500:
20 lemons or 3 cups fresh lemon juice
2 cups superfine sugar
4 cups water
3 tablespoons honey (optional)
answers.textarea_17284501:
1. Stir sugar in lemon juice until dissolved
2. Stir in the water
3. Optional: stir in honey
4. Add some ice, and it is ready to serve!
